# URL sync, live polling, and reopen flows

## Rule

URL query state, live events, polling, and reopen/hydration flows must not fight
each other.

## Requirements

1. Intentional detach/reset must clear the URL state and suppress automatic
   reattach in the same flow.
2. Optimistic placeholders must be written before attach/hydration, not after.
3. Socket subscriptions must have stable dependencies; use refs for changing data
   read by handlers.
4. Polling must back off when there is no in-flight work.
5. Shared lists should use a shared query key and pass data into children instead
   of spawning duplicate queries.
6. Reopen/hydrate must reset fields to defaults before applying saved values.
7. If saved data lacks overrides, clear prior overrides instead of leaking state
   from a previous item.
8. Toasts, banners, and status copy need one writer per message.

## Pre-commit check

- [ ] Detach clears URL and suppresses reattach.
- [ ] Socket handlers are stable.
- [ ] Polling backs off when idle.
- [ ] Reopen resets stale fields before applying saved data.
